{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":705,"text":"So imagine, you're in the supermarket,"},{"time":3355,"text":"you're buying some groceries,"},{"time":4936,"text":"and you get given the option"},{"time":6561,"text":"for a plastic or a paper shopping bag."},{"time":10196,"text":"Which one do you choose if you want to do"},{"time":12386,"text":"the right thing by the environment?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":14802,"text":"Most people do pick the paper."},{"time":16683,"text":"Okay, let's think of why."},{"time":17911,"text":"It's brown to start with."},{"time":19604,"text":"Therefore, it must be good for the environment."},{"time":21080,"text":"It's biodegradable. It's reusable."},{"time":23598,"text":"In some cases, it's recyclable."},{"time":25548,"text":"So when people are looking at the plastic bag,"},{"time":28342,"text":"it's likely they're thinking of something like this,"},{"time":31272,"text":"which we all know is absolutely terrible,"},{"time":33655,"text":"and we should be avoiding at all expenses"},{"time":35871,"text":"these kinds of environmental damages."},{"time":38226,"text":"But people are often not thinking"},{"time":40439,"text":"of something like this,"},{"time":42457,"text":"which is the other end of the spectrum."},{"time":45035,"text":"When we produce materials,"},{"time":47802,"text":"we need to extract them from the environment,"},{"time":49432,"text":"and we need a whole bunch\nof environmental impacts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53336,"text":"You see, what happens is, when we need"},{"time":55512,"text":"to make complex choices,"},{"time":57489,"text":"us humans like really simple solutions,"},{"time":59910,"text":"and so we often ask for simple solutions."},{"time":62526,"text":"And I work in design."},{"time":63999,"text":"I advise designers"},{"time":65510,"text":"and innovators around sustainability,"},{"time":67775,"text":"and everyone always says to me, \"Oh Leyla,"},{"time":69329,"text":"I just want the eco-materials.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":71251,"text":"And I say, \"Well, that's very complex,"},{"time":73535,"text":"and we'll have to spend four hours talking about"},{"time":75364,"text":"what exactly an eco-material means,"},{"time":77279,"text":"because everything at some point"},{"time":79199,"text":"comes from nature,"},{"time":81144,"text":"and it's how you use the material"},{"time":83239,"text":"that dictates the environmental impact."},{"time":86280,"text":"So what happens is, we have to rely"},{"time":88069,"text":"on some sort of intuitive framework"},{"time":90127,"text":"when we make decisions."},{"time":91702,"text":"So I like to call that intuitive framework"},{"time":94032,"text":"our environmental folklore."},{"time":96627,"text":"It's either the little voice\nat the back of your head,"},{"time":99384,"text":"or it's that gut feeling you get"},{"time":101656,"text":"when you've done the right thing,"},{"time":103236,"text":"so when you've picked the paper bag"},{"time":104784,"text":"or when you've bought a fuel-efficient car."},{"time":107899,"text":"And environmental folklore is a really important thing"},{"time":110858,"text":"because we're trying to do the right thing."},{"time":113306,"text":"But how do we know if we're actually"},{"time":115650,"text":"reducing the net environmental impacts"},{"time":117973,"text":"that our actions as individuals and as professionals"},{"time":121314,"text":"and as a society are actually having"},{"time":123482,"text":"on the natural environment?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":126187,"text":"So the thing about environmental folklore is"},{"time":128030,"text":"it tends to be based on our experiences,"},{"time":130085,"text":"the things we've heard from other people."},{"time":131816,"text":"It doesn't tend to be based\non any scientific framework."},{"time":134456,"text":"And this is really hard, because we live"},{"time":136123,"text":"in incredibly complex systems."},{"time":138143,"text":"We have the human systems"},{"time":139863,"text":"of how we communicate and interrelate"},{"time":141629,"text":"and have our whole constructed society,"},{"time":144144,"text":"We have the industrial systems,\nwhich is essentially the entire economy,"},{"time":148037,"text":"and then all of that has to operate"},{"time":149890,"text":"within the biggest system,"},{"time":151415,"text":"and, I would argue, the most important,"},{"time":153507,"text":"the ecosystem."},{"time":155163,"text":"And you see, the choices that we make"},{"time":157025,"text":"as an individual,"},{"time":158458,"text":"but the choices that we make"},{"time":159769,"text":"in every single job that we have,"},{"time":161928,"text":"no matter how high or low\nyou are in the pecking order,"},{"time":164548,"text":"has an impact on all of these systems."},{"time":167599,"text":"And the thing is that we have to find ways"},{"time":169934,"text":"if we're actually going to address sustainability"},{"time":171873,"text":"of interlocking those complex systems"},{"time":175021,"text":"and making better choices that result"},{"time":177965,"text":"in net environmental gains."},{"time":180549,"text":"What we need to do is we need to learn"},{"time":182197,"text":"to do more with less."},{"time":184273,"text":"We have an increasing population,"},{"time":186164,"text":"and everybody likes their mobile phones,"},{"time":187998,"text":"especially in this situation here."},{"time":190113,"text":"So we need to find innovative ways of solving\nsome of these problems that we face."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194168,"text":"And that's where this process called\nlife cycle thinking comes in."},{"time":197366,"text":"So essentially, everything that is created"},{"time":200053,"text":"goes through a series of life cycle stages,"},{"time":202564,"text":"and we use this scientific process"},{"time":204426,"text":"called life cycle assessment,"},{"time":206150,"text":"or in America, you guys say life cycle analysis,"},{"time":208891,"text":"in order to have a clearer picture of how"},{"time":212438,"text":"everything that we do in the\ntechnical part of those systems"},{"time":216244,"text":"affects the natural environment."},{"time":218025,"text":"So we go all the way back"},{"time":219995,"text":"to the extraction of raw materials,"},{"time":222198,"text":"and then we look at manufacturing,"},{"time":224015,"text":"we look at packaging and transportation,"},{"time":225874,"text":"use, and end of life,"},{"time":227524,"text":"and at every single one of these stages,"},{"time":230441,"text":"the things that we do"},{"time":231960,"text":"have an interaction with the natural environment,"},{"time":233791,"text":"and we can monitor how that interaction"},{"time":236279,"text":"is actually affecting the systems and services"},{"time":240009,"text":"that make life on Earth possible."},{"time":241924,"text":"And through doing this,"},{"time":243560,"text":"we've learned some absolutely fascinating things."},{"time":247850,"text":"And we've busted a bunch of myths."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249563,"text":"So to start with, there's a word that's used a lot."},{"time":254551,"text":"It's used a lot in marketing,"},{"time":256284,"text":"and it's used a lot, I think, in our conversation"},{"time":258284,"text":"when we're talking about sustainability,"},{"time":260217,"text":"and that's the word biodegradability."},{"time":262663,"text":"Now biodegradability is a material property;"},{"time":267611,"text":"it is not a definition of environmental benefits."},{"time":270859,"text":"Allow me to explain."},{"time":272762,"text":"When something natural,"},{"time":274454,"text":"something that's made from a cellulose fiber"},{"time":276415,"text":"like a piece of bread, even, or any food waste,"},{"time":279943,"text":"or even a piece of paper,"},{"time":282231,"text":"when something natural ends up"},{"time":284045,"text":"in the natural environment, it degrades normally."},{"time":286668,"text":"Its little carbon molecules that it stored up"},{"time":288532,"text":"as it was growing are naturally released"},{"time":290669,"text":"back into the atmosphere as carbon dioxide,"},{"time":293249,"text":"but this is a net situation."},{"time":295223,"text":"Most natural things"},{"time":296588,"text":"don't actually end up in nature."},{"time":298195,"text":"Most of the things, the waste that \nwe produce, end up in landfill."},{"time":301609,"text":"Landfill is a different environment."},{"time":304008,"text":"In landfill, those same carbon molecules"},{"time":306451,"text":"degrade in a different way,"},{"time":307969,"text":"because a landfill is anaerobic."},{"time":309881,"text":"It's got no oxygen. It's tightly compacted and hot."},{"time":313299,"text":"Those same molecules, they become methane,"},{"time":315647,"text":"and methane is a 25 times more potent"},{"time":318565,"text":"greenhouse gas than carbon dioxide."},{"time":321418,"text":"So our old lettuces and products"},{"time":324171,"text":"that we have thrown out that are made"},{"time":325750,"text":"out of biodegradable materials,"},{"time":327320,"text":"if they end up in landfill,"},{"time":329055,"text":"contribute to climate change."},{"time":331081,"text":"You see, there are facilities now"},{"time":332473,"text":"that can actually capture that methane"},{"time":334177,"text":"and generate power,"},{"time":335615,"text":"displacing the need for fossil fuel power,"},{"time":338406,"text":"but we need to be smart about this."},{"time":339871,"text":"We need to identify how we can start to leverage"},{"time":343036,"text":"these types of things that are already happening"},{"time":345340,"text":"and start to design systems and services"},{"time":347208,"text":"that alleviate these problems."},{"time":349091,"text":"Because right now, what people do\nis they turn around and they say,"},{"time":352336,"text":"\"Let's ban plastic bags. We'll give people paper"},{"time":354895,"text":"because that is better for the environment.\""},{"time":356822,"text":"But if you're throwing it in the bin,"},{"time":358240,"text":"and your local landfill facility"},{"time":359703,"text":"is just a normal one,"},{"time":362124,"text":"then we're having what's called a double negative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367030,"text":"I'm a product designer by trade."},{"time":370194,"text":"I then did social science."},{"time":371386,"text":"And so I'm absolutely fascinated"},{"time":372803,"text":"by consumer goods and how the consumer goods"},{"time":374802,"text":"that we have kind of become immune to"},{"time":376924,"text":"that fill our lives"},{"time":378162,"text":"have an impact on the natural environment."},{"time":379970,"text":"And these guys are, like, serial offenders,"},{"time":382583,"text":"and I'm pretty sure everyone in this room"},{"time":384446,"text":"has a refrigerator."},{"time":386076,"text":"Now America has this amazing ability"},{"time":387708,"text":"to keep growing refrigerators."},{"time":389717,"text":"In the last few years, they've grown one cubic foot"},{"time":391695,"text":"on average, the standard size"},{"time":393543,"text":"of a refrigerator."},{"time":395172,"text":"And the problem is, they're so big now,"},{"time":397631,"text":"it's easier for us to buy more food"},{"time":399825,"text":"that we can't eat or find."},{"time":401816,"text":"I mean, I have things at the back of my refrigerator"},{"time":403442,"text":"that have been there for years, all right?"},{"time":405652,"text":"And so what happens is, we waste more food."},{"time":408288,"text":"And as I was just explaining,\nfood waste is a problem."},{"time":411633,"text":"In fact, here in the U.S., 40 percent"},{"time":414995,"text":"of food purchased for the home is wasted."},{"time":417570,"text":"Half of the world's produced food is wasted."},{"time":421905,"text":"That's the latest U.N. stats. Up to half of the food."},{"time":424558,"text":"It's insane. It's 1.3 billion tons of food per annum."},{"time":429095,"text":"And I blame it on the refrigerator,"},{"time":431099,"text":"well, especially in Western cultures,"},{"time":432627,"text":"because it makes it easier."},{"time":434477,"text":"I mean, there's a lot of complex\nsystems going on here."},{"time":436869,"text":"I don't want to make it so simplistic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438807,"text":"But the refrigerator is a serious contributor to this,"},{"time":441757,"text":"and one of the features of it"},{"time":443615,"text":"is the crisper drawer."},{"time":445577,"text":"You all got crisper drawers?"},{"time":447078,"text":"The drawer that you put your lettuces in?"},{"time":449013,"text":"Lettuces have a habit of going soggy"},{"time":450933,"text":"in the crisper drawers, don't they?"},{"time":452729,"text":"Yeah? Soggy lettuces?"},{"time":454139,"text":"In the U.K., this is such a problem"},{"time":456139,"text":"that there was a government report a few years ago"},{"time":457837,"text":"that actually said the second biggest offender"},{"time":460857,"text":"of wasted food in the U.K. is the soggy lettuce."},{"time":463274,"text":"It was called the Soggy Lettuce Report."},{"time":465692,"text":"Okay? So this is a problem, people."},{"time":467905,"text":"These poor little lettuces are getting thrown out"},{"time":470015,"text":"left, right and center because the crisper drawers"},{"time":471887,"text":"are not designed to actually keep things crisp."},{"time":474646,"text":"Okay. You need a tight environment."},{"time":476855,"text":"You need, like, an airless environment"},{"time":478985,"text":"to prevent the degrading that\nwould happen naturally."},{"time":481710,"text":"But the crisper drawers, they're just a drawer"},{"time":483662,"text":"with a slightly better seal."},{"time":485370,"text":"Anyway, I'm clearly obsessed."},{"time":487457,"text":"Don't ever invite me over because I'll just\nstart going through your refrigerator"},{"time":490182,"text":"and looking at all sorts of things like that."},{"time":491700,"text":"But essentially, this is a big problem."},{"time":493619,"text":"Because when we lose something\nlike the lettuce from the system,"},{"time":496578,"text":"not only do we have that impact \nI just explained at the end of life,"},{"time":500114,"text":"but we actually have had to grow that lettuce."},{"time":502770,"text":"The life cycle impact of that lettuce is astronomical."},{"time":506041,"text":"We've had to clear land."},{"time":507459,"text":"We've had to plant seeds, phosphorus,"},{"time":509616,"text":"fertilizers, nutrients, water, sunlight."},{"time":511740,"text":"All of the embodied impacts in that lettuce"},{"time":513828,"text":"get lost from the system,"},{"time":515540,"text":"which makes it a far bigger environmental impact"},{"time":518151,"text":"than the loss of the energy from the fridge."},{"time":521835,"text":"So we need to design things like this far better"},{"time":525100,"text":"if we're going to start addressing\nserious environmental problems."},{"time":528281,"text":"We could start with the crisper drawer and the size."},{"time":529932,"text":"For those of you in the room who do design fridges,"},{"time":531684,"text":"that would be great."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533177,"text":"The problem is, imagine if we"},{"time":536275,"text":"actually started to reconsider \nhow we designed things."},{"time":538925,"text":"So I look at the refrigerator as a sign of modernity,"},{"time":542532,"text":"but we actually haven't really changed the design"},{"time":544630,"text":"of them that much since the 1950s."},{"time":547301,"text":"A little bit, but essentially they're still big boxes,"},{"time":550526,"text":"cold boxes that we store stuff in."},{"time":552448,"text":"So imagine if we actually really started"},{"time":554268,"text":"to identify these problems and use that"},{"time":557013,"text":"as the foundation for finding innovative and elegant"},{"time":560950,"text":"design solutions that will solve those problems."},{"time":564303,"text":"This is design-led system change,"},{"time":566528,"text":"design dictating the way in which the system"},{"time":570238,"text":"can be far more sustainable."},{"time":573003,"text":"Forty percent food waste is a major problem."},{"time":575097,"text":"Imagine if we designed fridges that halved that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579162,"text":"Another item that I find fascinating"},{"time":581513,"text":"is the electric tea kettle,"},{"time":582766,"text":"which I found out that"},{"time":584159,"text":"you don't do tea kettles in\nthis country, really, do you?"},{"time":587410,"text":"But that's really big in the U.K."},{"time":589498,"text":"Ninety-seven percent of households"},{"time":591731,"text":"in the United Kingdom own an electric tea kettle."},{"time":594663,"text":"So they're very popular."},{"time":596270,"text":"And, I mean, if I were to work with a design firm"},{"time":599070,"text":"or a designer, and they were designing one of these,"},{"time":601322,"text":"and they wanted to do it eco,"},{"time":602561,"text":"they'd usually ask me two things."},{"time":604479,"text":"They'd say, \"Leyla, how do I\nmake it technically efficient?\""},{"time":607523,"text":"Because obviously energy's\na problem with this product."},{"time":610811,"text":"Or, \"How do I make it green materials?"},{"time":613876,"text":"How do I make the materials green"},{"time":616786,"text":"in the manufacturing?\""},{"time":618608,"text":"Would you ask me those questions?"},{"time":620411,"text":"They seem logical, right? Yeah."},{"time":623210,"text":"Well I'd say, \"You're looking at the wrong problems.\""},{"time":625769,"text":"Because the problem is with use."},{"time":627927,"text":"It's with how people use the product."},{"time":630602,"text":"Sixty-five percent of Brits"},{"time":632437,"text":"admit to over-filling their kettle"},{"time":634781,"text":"when they only need one cup of tea."},{"time":637367,"text":"All of this extra water that's being boiled"},{"time":640110,"text":"requires energy, and it's been calculated"},{"time":644078,"text":"that in one day of extra energy use"},{"time":647116,"text":"from boiling kettles"},{"time":648659,"text":"is enough to light all of the streetlights"},{"time":651301,"text":"in England for a night."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653924,"text":"But this is the thing."},{"time":656042,"text":"This is what I call a product-person failure."},{"time":657956,"text":"But we've got a product-system failure\ngoing on with these little guys,"},{"time":660702,"text":"and they're so ubiquitous, you \ndon't even notice they're there."},{"time":663612,"text":"And this guy over here, though, he does.\nHe's named Simon."},{"time":666825,"text":"Simon works for the national\nelectricity company in the U.K."},{"time":670132,"text":"He has a very important job of monitoring"},{"time":672274,"text":"all of the electricity coming into the system"},{"time":674713,"text":"to make sure there is enough"},{"time":676126,"text":"so it powers everybody's homes."},{"time":678054,"text":"He's also watching television."},{"time":680158,"text":"The reason is because there's a unique"},{"time":682131,"text":"phenomenon that happens in the U.K."},{"time":683949,"text":"the moment that very popular TV shows end."},{"time":687987,"text":"The minute the ad break comes on,"},{"time":690225,"text":"this man has to rush"},{"time":692062,"text":"to buy nuclear power from France,"},{"time":695118,"text":"because everybody turns their kettles on"},{"time":698007,"text":"at the same time."},{"time":700072,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":702318,"text":"1.5 million kettles, seriously problematic."},{"time":708303,"text":"So imagine if you designed kettles,"},{"time":711872,"text":"you actually found a way to\nsolve these system failures,"},{"time":714612,"text":"because this is a huge amount of pressure"},{"time":717277,"text":"on the system,"},{"time":718668,"text":"just because the product hasn't\nthought about the problem"},{"time":722104,"text":"that it's going to have when it exists in the world."},{"time":723967,"text":"Now, I looked at a number of\nkettles available on the market,"},{"time":726635,"text":"and found the minimum fill lines,"},{"time":728657,"text":"so the little piece of information that tells you"},{"time":730423,"text":"how much you need to put in there,"},{"time":731980,"text":"was between two and a five-and-a-half cups of water"},{"time":734899,"text":"just to make one cup of tea."},{"time":738332,"text":"So this kettle here is an example of one where"},{"time":740617,"text":"it actually has two reservoirs."},{"time":743155,"text":"One's a boiling chamber, and one's the water holder."},{"time":745340,"text":"The user actually has to push that button"},{"time":747665,"text":"to get their hot water boiled,"},{"time":749233,"text":"which means, because we're all lazy,"},{"time":750999,"text":"you only fill exactly what you need."},{"time":752841,"text":"And this is what I call behavior-changing products:"},{"time":755165,"text":"products, systems or services"},{"time":757277,"text":"that intervene and solve these problems up front."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761136,"text":"Now, this is a technology arena,"},{"time":763786,"text":"so obviously these things are quite popular,"},{"time":765847,"text":"but I think if we're going to keep"},{"time":767815,"text":"designing, buying and using and throwing out"},{"time":770401,"text":"these kinds of products at the rate we currently do,"},{"time":772313,"text":"which is astronomically high,"},{"time":774562,"text":"there are seven billion people"},{"time":776396,"text":"who live in the world right now."},{"time":777806,"text":"There are six billion mobile phone subscriptions"},{"time":779993,"text":"as of last year."},{"time":783659,"text":"Every single year, 1.5 billion mobile phones"},{"time":787181,"text":"roll off production lines,"},{"time":788434,"text":"and some companies report their production rate"},{"time":790505,"text":"as being greater than the human birth rate."},{"time":792855,"text":"One hundred fifty-two million phones \nwere thrown out in the U.S. last year;"},{"time":795985,"text":"only 11 percent were recycled."},{"time":797869,"text":"I'm from Australia. We have a\npopulation of 22 million -- don't laugh --"},{"time":801227,"text":"and it's been reported that 22 million phones"},{"time":804300,"text":"are in people's drawers."},{"time":806907,"text":"We need to find ways of solving\nthe problems around this,"},{"time":810628,"text":"because these things are so complicated."},{"time":813525,"text":"They have so much locked up inside them."},{"time":816831,"text":"Gold! Did you know that it's actually cheaper now"},{"time":820594,"text":"to get gold out of a ton of old mobile phones"},{"time":824211,"text":"than it is out of a ton of gold ore?"},{"time":827439,"text":"There's a number of highly complex and valuable"},{"time":829829,"text":"materials embodied inside these things,"},{"time":831430,"text":"so we need to find ways of encouraging disassembly,"},{"time":833888,"text":"because this is otherwise what happens."},{"time":836052,"text":"This is a community in Ghana,"},{"time":837726,"text":"and e-waste is reported, or electronic waste"},{"time":839984,"text":"is reported by the U.N."},{"time":841960,"text":"as being up to 50 million tons trafficked."},{"time":844992,"text":"This is how they get the gold"},{"time":846306,"text":"and the other valuable materials out."},{"time":847840,"text":"They burn the electronic waste"},{"time":849778,"text":"in open spaces."},{"time":851809,"text":"These are communities, and this\nis happening all over the world."},{"time":854944,"text":"And because we don't see the ramifications"},{"time":857491,"text":"of the choices that we make as designers,"},{"time":859320,"text":"as businesspeople, as consumers,"},{"time":861790,"text":"then these kinds of externalities happen,"},{"time":863403,"text":"and these are people's lives."},{"time":865705,"text":"So we need to find smarter, more systems-based,"},{"time":870153,"text":"innovative solutions to these problems,"},{"time":873069,"text":"if we're going to start to live\nsustainably within this world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":876845,"text":"So imagine if, when you bought your mobile phone,"},{"time":880818,"text":"your new one because you replaced your old one --"},{"time":882508,"text":"after 15 to 18 months is the average time"},{"time":884883,"text":"that people replace their phones, by the way â€”"},{"time":886987,"text":"so if we're going to keep this kind of expedient"},{"time":889972,"text":"mobile phone replacing, then we should"},{"time":892210,"text":"be looking at closing the loop on these systems."},{"time":894259,"text":"The people who produce these phones,"},{"time":896170,"text":"and some of which I'm sure\nare in the room right now,"},{"time":897999,"text":"could potentially look at doing what\nwe call closed-loop systems,"},{"time":900677,"text":"or product system services,"},{"time":902245,"text":"so identifying that there is a market demand"},{"time":904507,"text":"and that market demand's not going to go anywhere,"},{"time":906324,"text":"so you design the product to solve the problem."},{"time":909377,"text":"Design for disassembly, design for light-weighting."},{"time":911716,"text":"We heard some of those kinds of strategies"},{"time":914082,"text":"being used in the Tesla Motors car today."},{"time":916941,"text":"These kinds of approaches are not hard,"},{"time":919053,"text":"but understanding the system"},{"time":920911,"text":"and then looking for viable, market-driven"},{"time":924442,"text":"consumer demand alternatives"},{"time":926425,"text":"is how we can start radically altering"},{"time":928976,"text":"the sustainability agenda,"},{"time":930783,"text":"because I hate to break it to you all:"},{"time":932654,"text":"Consumption is the biggest problem."},{"time":935457,"text":"But design is one of the best solutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940719,"text":"These kinds of products are everywhere."},{"time":942903,"text":"By identifying alternative ways of doing things,"},{"time":945571,"text":"we can actually start to innovate,"},{"time":947166,"text":"and I say actually start to innovate."},{"time":948559,"text":"I'm sure everyone in this room is very innovative."},{"time":951044,"text":"But in the regards to using sustainability"},{"time":953398,"text":"as a parameter, as a criteria"},{"time":956085,"text":"for fueling systems-based solutions,"},{"time":960302,"text":"because as I've just demonstrated\nwith these simple products,"},{"time":963207,"text":"they're participating in these major problems."},{"time":966598,"text":"So we need to look across the entire life"},{"time":968753,"text":"of the things that we do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":970375,"text":"If you just had paper or plastic --"},{"time":972090,"text":"obviously reusable is far more beneficial --"},{"time":974854,"text":"then the paper is worse,"},{"time":978325,"text":"and the paper is worse because it weighs"},{"time":980371,"text":"four to 10 times more than the plastic,"},{"time":982475,"text":"and when we actually compare,\nfrom a life cycle perspective,"},{"time":984842,"text":"a kilo of plastic and a kilo of paper,"},{"time":987532,"text":"the paper is far better,"},{"time":989178,"text":"but the functionality of a plastic or a paper bag"},{"time":991718,"text":"to carry your groceries home is not \ndone with a kilo of each material."},{"time":995333,"text":"It's done with a very small amount of plastic"},{"time":997302,"text":"and quite a lot more paper."},{"time":998995,"text":"Because functionality defines environmental impact,"},{"time":1001953,"text":"and I said earlier that the designers\nalways ask me for the eco-materials."},{"time":1004786,"text":"I say, there's only a few materials\nthat you should completely avoid."},{"time":1007831,"text":"The rest of them, it's all about application,"},{"time":1009730,"text":"and at the end of the day, everything\nwe design and produce in the economy"},{"time":1012749,"text":"or buy as consumers is done so for function."},{"time":1015089,"text":"We want something, therefore we buy it."},{"time":1017206,"text":"So breaking things back down and delivering"},{"time":1020362,"text":"smartly, elegantly, sophisticated solutions"},{"time":1024361,"text":"that take into consideration the entire system"},{"time":1027158,"text":"and the entire life of the thing, everything,"},{"time":1030253,"text":"all the way back to the extraction\nthrough to the end of life,"},{"time":1033089,"text":"we can start to actually find\nreally innovative solutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1035891,"text":"And I'll just leave you with one very quick thing"},{"time":1037961,"text":"that a designer said to me recently \nwho I work with, a senior designer."},{"time":1041818,"text":"I said, \"How come you're not doing \nsustainability? I know you know this.\""},{"time":1044916,"text":"And he said, \"Well, recently I pitched\na sustainability project to a client,"},{"time":1048928,"text":"and turned and he said to me,"},{"time":1050869,"text":"'I know it's going to cost less,"},{"time":1052634,"text":"I know it's going to sell more,"},{"time":1054252,"text":"but we're not pioneers, because\npioneers have arrows in their backs.'\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1058725,"text":"I think we've got a roomful of pioneers,"},{"time":1060942,"text":"and I hope there are far more pioneers out there,\nbecause we need to solve these problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1064027,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1065434,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}